Method Detail

nextLexeme

public int nextLexeme()
               throws java.io.IOException
Gets the next lexeme from the input stream and returns an integer code indicating its type: LT_EOF, LT_EOL, LT_SLASHSLASH, LT_SLASHASTER, LT_SLASHASTERASTER, or LT_LEXEME. If it is a lexeme, the String value is in the public String, theLexeme. Error conditions (unterminated strings and comments) may also be returned.
Returns:
Code indicating type of lexeme found.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if there is an error reading the file.
